    <properties>
        <title>Mod4j 1.3.0 Release Notes</title>
    </properties>
    <body>
        <section name="Mod4j 1.3.0 Release Notes">

            <p>
                Dear Mod4j community,
                <br />
                <br />
                The Mod4j development team is pleased to announce the release of Mod4j 1.3.0.
                The
                following list highlights the
                main issues that were involved with this release. For
                the complete list of solved bugs, improvements and tasks,
                scroll down to the Release
                Notes List.
                <br />
                With this release you should be prepared to take extra time for some refactoring,
                because there is a
                breaking change involved. You can read more about this chang in
                the
                <a href="upgradenotes.html">Mod4j 1.3.0 Upgrade Notes</a>
            </p>

            <subsection name="How to upgrade">
                <p>
                    If you want to upgrade from the previous Mod4j release, you will need to follow
                    the required upgrade steps
                    as described in the
                    <a href="upgradenotes.html">Mod4j 1.3.0 Upgrade Notes</a>
                </p>
            </subsection>
            <subsection name="1.3.0 Relaese Notes List">

                <h2>Bug</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        [
                        <a href='http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MODFORJ-149'>MODFORJ-149</a>
                        ] - Mod4j classnames should be validated
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        [
                        <a href='http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MODFORJ-193'>MODFORJ-193</a>
                        ] - Invalid constructor generated in the example class of a subclass
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        [
                        <a href='http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MODFORJ-208'>MODFORJ-208</a>
                        ] - ConcurrentUpdateException
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        [
                        <a href='http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MODFORJ-210'>MODFORJ-210</a>
                        ] - LazyInitializationException when an update generates
                        BusinessRuleException
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        [
                        <a href='http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MODFORJ-218'>MODFORJ-218</a>
                        ] - Derived attributes not translated
                    </li>
                </ul>

                <h2>Improvement</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        [
                        <a href='http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/MODFORJ-189'>MODFORJ-189</a>
                        ] - Streamline exception handling over all layers in the architecture
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </subsection>
        </section>
    </body>
</document>
